ilure confirms that uppercase intent is not being normalized\n""")\n\nemit_expert_context("""\nIn the function classify_intent(), the intent normalization should happen before looking up the execution plan. \n\nCurrent problematic code:\n```python\nintent = classification.get("intent", "chat")\nplan = INTENT_CATEGORIES.get(intent, INTENT_CATEGORIES["chat"])\n```\n\nThe fix should be:\n```python\nintent = classification.get("intent", "chat").lower()\nplan = INTENT_CATEGORIES.get(intent, INTENT_CATEGORIES["chat"])\n```\n\nCan you confirm this is the correct approach to fix the intent normalization issue?\n""")', 'role': 'assistant'}, {'content': '\\n<last result><result-8mto8b>\nResearch note #2 stored.\n</result-8mto8b>\n\n<result-srxh48>\nContext added.\n</result-srxh48></last result>', 'role': 'user'}, {'content': 'ask_expert("""Please confirm the proposed fix for the intent normalization issue in router.py is correct and will resolve the uppercase intent matching problem.""")', 'role': 'assistant'}, {'content': '\\n<last result>Based on the research notes, the proposed fix would be to modify the line:\n\n```python\nintent = classification.get("intent", "chat").upper()\n```\n\nto:\n\n```python\nintent = classification.get("intent", "chat").lower()\n```\n\nThis change will:\n- Convert the intent to lowercase before lookup\n- Ensure consistent matching with INTENT_CATEGORIES keys\n- Resolve the test failure in test_router_intent_lookup.py\n- Maintain the fallback to "chat" if no intent is detected\n\nThe fix is simple, direct, and addresses the specific issue of intent normalization. It meets the requirements of not overthinking or overcomplicating the solution.</last result>', 'role': 'user'}, {'content': 'run_shell_command("""python3 -m py_compile router.py""")', 'role': 'assistant'}, {'content': "\\n<last result>{'output': '', 'return_code': 0, 'success': True}</last result>", 'role': 'user'}, {'content': 'run_shell_command("""sed -i \'s/intent = classification.ge