eative\n   - analysis\n   - chat\n\n2. classify_intent() function workflow:\n   - Uses OpenRouter API to classify query\n   - Handles JSON parsing from LLM response\n   - Matches intent to INTENT_CATEGORIES\n   - Assigns execution plan based on intent\n\n3. Potential Issue Location:\n   - Line with `intent = classification.get("intent", "chat").lower()`\n   - Ensures lowercase intent matching\n   - Prevents uppercase intent lookup failures\n\nValidation Required:\n- Confirm lowercase normalization works correctly\n- Verify all intent categories are accessible\n- Check fallback to "chat" intent works as expected\n\n\nRouter Intent Classification Bug Research:\n\nLocation: router.py\nBug: Intent classification fails with uppercase intent strings\nCurrent Behavior: \n- Intent lookup does not normalize case\n- Uppercase intents like "CODE" fall back to "chat" category\n- Prevents correct intent routing\n\nKey Findings:\n1. INTENT_CATEGORIES contains lowercase keys\n2. classify_intent() needs lowercase normalization\n3. Proposed fix: Add .lower() to intent retrieval\n\nVerification Steps:\n- Lowercase normalization added\n- All tests in test_router_intent_lookup.py passed\n- No changes to unrelated files\n- Py_compile check successful\n\nRecommended Fix:\nChange: `intent = classification.get("intent", "chat").lower()`\nPurpose: Normalize intent case before lookup\n\n\nRouter Intent Classification Bug Research:\n\nBug Location: router.py\nSpecific Issue: Intent classification fails with uppercase intent strings\n\nKey Findings:\n1. INTENT_CATEGORIES contains lowercase keys\n2. classify_intent() requires lowercase normalization\n3. Current implementation does not handle case-insensitive intent matching\n\nVerification Steps Completed:\n- Examined router.py contents\n- Ran tests in test_router_intent_lookup.py\n- Confirmed py_compile check passed\n- Validated lowercase normalization fix\n\nProposed Solution:\nModify intent retrieval to use .lower() method:\n`intent = classification.get("intent", "chat").lower()`\n\nThis ensures:\n- Uppercase intents are normalized\n- Correct intent routing\n- Fallback to "chat" works as expected\n\nTest Validation:\n- All 3 tests in test_router_intent_lookup.py passed\n- No changes to unrelated files\n- Py_compile check successful\n</research notes>\n\n<environment inventory>\n**Operating System:** Linux (Ubuntu 24.04.4 LTS 24.04)\n\n**Found CLI developer tools:** fd, rg, fzf, git (git version 2.43.0), g++ (g++ (Ubuntu 13.3.0-6ubuntu2~24.04.1) 13.3.0), gcc (gcc (Ubuntu 13.3.0-6ubuntu2~24.04.1) 13.3.0), make, pkg-config\n\n**Python Environments:**\n- Python 3.11.14 at `/home/exedev/.hermes/hermes-agent/venv/bin/python3.11`\n- Python 3.12.3 at `/home/exedev/autonomy/labs/agent-harness-bakeoff/.venv-raaid/bin/python3`\n- Python 3.12.3 at `/home/exedev/autonomy/labs/agent-harness-bakeoff/.venv-raaid/bin/python`\n- Python 3.12.3 at `/home/exedev/autonomy/labs/agent-harness-bakeoff/.venv-raaid/bin/python3.12`\n- venv (builtin): available\n- virtualenv: installed (version virtualenv 21.2.0 from /home/exedev/.local/lib/python3.12/site-packages/virtualenv/__init__.py)\n- uv: installed (version 0.10.4)\n- pipenv: not installed\n- poetry: not installed\n- conda: not installed\n- pyenv: not installed\n- pipx: installed (version 1.4.3)\n\n**Package Managers:**\n- apt: found (apt 2.8.3 (amd64))\n- apt-get: found (apt 2.8.3 (amd64))\n\n**Developer Libraries:**\n- zlib: installed (version 1.3), libs: `-lz`\n- ICU: installed (version 74.2), libs: `-licuuc -licudata`\n- Not found: APR, Allegro, Armadillo, Assimp, BLAS, BerkeleyDB, Blaze, Blitz++, Boost, BoostTest, Boost_Asio, Boost_Beast, Boost_uBLAS, BoringSSL, Botan, Box2D, Brotli, Bullet, CMake, CUDA, Caffe, Cairo, ChakraCore, Crypto++, DearImGui, DirectX, Duktape, Eigen, FFmpeg, FMOD, GLFW, GLM, GLib, GSL, GStreamer, GTK, GnuTLS, GoogleTest, Guile, HDF5, HIP, IntelMKL, Irrlicht, Jack, JavaScriptCore, JoltPhysics, LAPACK, LZ4, LevelDB, LibreSSL, LightGBM, Lua, LuaJI